At 10:35 AM 10/20/99 +1000, you wrote:
>I'm still fiddling around trying to get the VOX recording system to work. I
>have installed DirectX 7, and DMDX 1.1.12. When I press the VOX button on
>the DMDX main console, with no tasks running in the background, I get the
>following message:
>
>DirectSoundCaptureCreate failed
>DSERR_ALLOCATED (8878000a)
>The call failed because resources (such as a priority level) were already
>being used by another caller.
>
>Can anybody interpret this for me? Even better, has anyone had this problem
>themselves, and does anyone know how to fix it?

  How old is the sound card you are trying to use this with?  Most older
cards do not have sufficient resources to allow simultaneous playback and
recording.  Perhaps you do not have sufficient resources allocated to the
sound card (like two DMA channels).

